      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. B. Ministry of environment and forests and climate change</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Explanation -&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Bio-Medical Waste&nbsp;</strong>(Management and Handling) Rule was prescribed by the <strong>Ministry of Environment</strong> and <strong>Forests and climate change (MOEFCC), Government of India</strong>.&nbsp;Under<strong> Legislation</strong> - <strong>Sections 6, 8</strong> and <strong>25 </strong>of<strong> Environment (Protection) Act, 1986</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">These rules shall <strong>not</strong> apply to <strong>Radioactive wastes, Hazardous chemicals</strong>, <strong>Municipal solid wastes</strong>, <strong>Lead acid batteries, Hazardous wastes</strong>, <strong>e-Waste</strong>, <strong>Hazardous micro-organisms</strong>, <strong>Genetically engineered microorganisms.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">BMW - emblem</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2023/10/23/image_V60HOwu.png\" width=\"610\" height=\"212\"></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Educational objective:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Biomedical Wastes (BMW)&nbsp;</strong>in India are <strong>handled</strong> and <strong>managed </strong>under ‘<strong>Biomedical Waste Management</strong> (Management and Handling) Rules, <strong>1998’.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Exercising powers</strong>: Sections <strong>6, 8, 25</strong> of ‘Environmental (Protection) <strong>Act, 1986’</strong> (under the <strong>Ministry of Environment and Forests and climate change</strong>)</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Reference: Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed pg. 886</strong></span></p>",
